## Architecture Reference

### Message Types Hierarchy

```typescript
// Core types (pi-ai)
interface UserMessage {
  role: "user";
  content: string | (TextContent | ImageContent)[];
  timestamp: number;
}

interface AssistantMessage {
  role: "assistant";
  content: (TextContent | ThinkingContent | ToolCall)[];
  api: Api;              // "anthropic-messages", "openai-chat", etc.
  provider: Provider;    // "anthropic", "openai", etc.
  model: string;         // "claude-sonnet-4-20250514"
  responseId?: string;   // Provider response ID
  usage: Usage;
  stopReason: StopReason;
  errorMessage?: string;
  timestamp: number;
  incomplete?: boolean;  // NEW: for continuation feature
}

// Extended types (coding-agent)
interface BashExecutionMessage {
  role: "bashExecution";
  command: string;
  output: string;
  exitCode: number | undefined;
  excludeFromContext?: boolean;  // !! prefix
  // ...
}

interface CustomMessage {
  role: "custom";
  customType: string;    // Extension identifier
  content: string | (TextContent | ImageContent)[];
  display: boolean;
  details?: any;         // NOT sent to LLM
  // ...
}
```

### Session Entry Types

```typescript
type SessionEntry =
  | SessionMessageEntry      // AgentMessage with id/parentId
  | ModelChangeEntry         // provider, modelId
  | ThinkingLevelChangeEntry // thinkingLevel
  | CompactionEntry          // summary, firstKeptEntryId
  | BranchSummaryEntry       // fromId, summary
  | CustomEntry              // Extension state (NOT in LLM context)
  | CustomMessageEntry       // Extension message (IN LLM context)
  | LabelEntry               // User bookmarks
```

### Transformation Pipeline

```typescript
// 1. Session → AgentMessage[]
const { messages } = sessionManager.buildSessionContext(entries, leafId);

// 2. AgentMessage[] → Message[]
const llmMessages = convertToLlm(messages);
  // Handles: bashExecution → user, custom → user, branchSummary → user, etc.

// 3. Message[] → Message[] (cross-provider)
const normalized = transformMessages(llmMessages, model);
  // Handles: thinking blocks, tool call ID normalization, orphaned tool calls

// 4. Message[] → Provider format (inside provider)
const request = convertToProviderFormat(normalized, model, tools);
```

