## Incomplete Messages: Full Plan

### Goal

Enable extensions to inject an "incomplete" assistant message that the agent will naturally continue from.

### Use Case

```
User: /sh -i ls -la
    ↓
Extension injects: AssistantMessage "I need to check the files..." (incomplete: true)
    ↓
Agent continues: "...in this directory. [executes bash tool] [reports results]"
```

### Implementation Details

#### Phase 1: Type Definition

```typescript
// packages/ai/src/types.ts
export interface AssistantMessage {
    // ... existing fields
    incomplete?: boolean;  // If true, agent should continue from this message
}
```

#### Phase 2: Agent Loop

```typescript
// packages/agent/src/agent-loop.ts

// In runLoop, after streaming response:
if (message.incomplete) {
    // Emit turn_end but NOT agent_end
    await emit({ type: "turn_end", message, toolResults: [] });
    continue;  // Continue outer loop for next response
}
```

#### Phase 3: AgentSession API

```typescript
// packages/coding-agent/src/core/agent-session.ts

async sendAssistantMessage(
    content: string | (TextContent | ThinkingContent)[],
    options?: {
        thinking?: boolean;
        deliverAs?: "steer" | "followUp" | "nextTurn";
        incomplete?: boolean;  // NEW
    }
): Promise<void> {
    const assistantMessage: AssistantMessage = {
        // ...
        incomplete: options?.incomplete,
    };

    this.agent.state.messages.push(assistantMessage);

    // If incomplete and agent idle, trigger continuation
    if (options?.incomplete && !this.isStreaming) {
        await this.agent.continue();
    }
}
```

